p: The chemical profiles of the EOs of different P. guajava varieties are shown in Table 1. A total of 38 chemical compounds were identified in the EOs of the studied guava varieties. The WI variety attained the highest number of compounds (29), while RM, ESEG, RI, E, and EQ had 28, 26, 25, 23, and 20 compounds, respectively. This composition was relatively higher than those reported for the Tunisian variety [ 26].
